<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-12"><hi rend="italic">November 12,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 663.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In acknowledging the receipt of your No.
                            652, of the 24th ultimo, I have to approve your demand that the grand
                            vizier’s orders for bringing Guedjian to Constantinople be carried
                            out.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>